snippet: Contrary to conventional wisdom, an accumulation of the gooey bodies at the bottom of the ocean draws scavengers and is a key part of the food chain.
abstract: Research shows that ocean's bottom-feeders are just as enthusiastic about gobbling up dead jellyfish as other types of fish, contradicting previous assumptions; findings provide reassurance that increasing jellyfish populations will find important role in food chain.
lead_paragraph: Contrary to conventional wisdom, an accumulation of the gooey bodies at the bottom of the ocean draws scavengers and is a key part of the food chain.
